    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🚀 Workflow 1 — Application Ingestion & AI Screening\n\n**Trigger:** Every 2 hours\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Reads new applications from both SWE and BDM Google Sheets\n2. Normalises column names into a unified schema\n3. Deduplicates against Supabase (skips already-processed candidates)\n4. Downloads each resume from Google Drive (handles both URL formats)\n5. Extracts text from PDF\n6. Builds a role-specific AI prompt and sends to Gemini (Groq as fallback)\n7. Safely parses AI JSON output — never crashes on malformed responses\n8. Stores full candidate record + AI assessment in Supabase with status = pending\n9. Sends a confirmation email (HTML) to the candidate\n\n**Assumptions:**\n- Resume files are PDFs uploaded via Google Form (stored in Google Drive)\n- Supabase table: `candidates` with columns matching field IDs below\n- Supabase table: `available_slots` with `slot_start`, `slot_end`, `is_booked`, `booked_by`",
        "height": 428,
        "width": 644,
        "color": 5
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -2816,
        -976
      ],
      "id": "381c48d0-b731-44e7-811a-2d44e912ead1",
      "name": "Note — Workflow 1 Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 📧 Workflow 2 — Email Dispatch & Scheduling\n\n**Trigger:** Every 12 hours (decoupled from ingestion)\n\n**What it does:**\n1. Fetches all candidates with status = `pending` from Supabase\n2. If none found → exits gracefully with no errors\n3. Loops one-by-one through pending candidates\n4. Routes by AI classification:\n   - **Strong** → checks available interview slots → creates Google Calendar event with candidate as attendee → sends HTML interview invitation email\n   - **Strong (no slots)** → sends holding email, sets status = `slots_full` for retry\n   - **Average** → sends HTML manual review notification to hiring manager\n   - **Weak** → sends HTML soft rejection email to candidate\n5. Updates candidate status to `processed` after email sent",
        "height": 436,
        "width": 576,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
